<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="498" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[491,1527,280,685]" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">
Diagnosis (Female) — Prodorsum centrally with strong areolae, posteriorly reticulation with large cells, anteriorly weakly reticulate, with setae short and serrate, setae 
<emphasis box="[1352,1377,314,338]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">v2</emphasis>
shortest; opisthosoma between setae 
<emphasis box="[789,814,349,373]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">c1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[867,896,349,373]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">d1</emphasis>
smooth to weakly reticulate, cuticle between 
<emphasis box="[1384,1413,349,373]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">d1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1463,1488,349,373]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">e1</emphasis>
weakly reticulate or wrinkled, between 
<emphasis box="[908,933,384,408]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">e1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[983,1010,384,408]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">h1</emphasis>
with strong V-shaped folds, mediolateral with reticulations, transverse folds behind setae 
<emphasis box="[945,970,418,442]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">e1</emphasis>
; setae 
<emphasis box="[1042,1063,418,442]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">f2</emphasis>
absent with marginal setae short, serrate,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[491,1527,280,685]" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">
3 pairs of short, serrate dorsocentral setae (
<figureCitation box="[964,1062,453,477]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="17.[119,186,1808,1829]" captionTargetBox="[231,1366,374,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-2@17.[231,1366,374,1754]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 11 Brevipalpus yothersiBaker – Female: A – dorsal view; B – opisthogaster; C – spermatheca; Deutonymph: D – dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5399552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5399552/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">Fig 11A</figureCitation>
); ventral and genital shields verrucose and verrucose-reticulate, respectively (
<figureCitation box="[910,1016,487,511]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="17.[119,186,1808,1829]" captionTargetBox="[231,1366,374,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-2@17.[231,1366,374,1754]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 11 Brevipalpus yothersiBaker – Female: A – dorsal view; B – opisthogaster; C – spermatheca; Deutonymph: D – dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5399552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5399552/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
); rostrum extends to about middle of femur
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[491,1527,280,685]" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">
I; palp tarsus II with 2 solenidia distally; palp femorogenu with dorsal seta narrow, serrate; spermathecal terminates into a sclerotised oval vesicle with a thick distal stipe (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1446,556,580]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="17.[119,186,1808,1829]" captionTargetBox="[231,1366,374,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-2@17.[231,1366,374,1754]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 11 Brevipalpus yothersiBaker – Female: A – dorsal view; B – opisthogaster; C – spermatheca; Deutonymph: D – dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5399552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5399552/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">Fig 11C</figureCitation>
). Deutonymph — Prodorsal setae 
<emphasis box="[874,899,591,615]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">v2</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[949,1007,591,615]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">sc1-2</emphasis>
broadly lanceolate, but with 
<emphasis box="[1312,1337,591,615]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">v2</emphasis>
short; opisthosomal setae 
<emphasis box="[620,725,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">c1, d1, e1</emphasis>
minute, setae 
<emphasis box="[873,976,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">c3, d3, e3</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[988,1088,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">f3, h1, h2</emphasis>
large and broadly lanceolate, but setae 
<emphasis box="[491,560,660,684]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">c3, d3</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[608,634,660,684]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">e3</emphasis>
can vary from short to large (
<figureCitation box="[957,1054,660,684]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="17.[119,186,1808,1829]" captionTargetBox="[231,1366,374,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-2@17.[231,1366,374,1754]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 11 Brevipalpus yothersiBaker – Female: A – dorsal view; B – opisthogaster; C – spermatheca; Deutonymph: D – dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5399552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5399552/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="498">Fig 11D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
